latestIgtvVideos.title: Skin food: Papaya and Banana face mask.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Ingredients:
1tbsp of whole milk
A small piece of mashed papaya
A small piece of over-ripped banana 
1-11/2tsp of Quaker Oats( crushed ones)
1/2 tsp virgin coconut oil
1 tsp honey ( Amritam saffron honey @goodearthindia )
Mix all the ingredients in a bowl  to a paste or a purée consistency .
Apply for 15-20 mins , then remove with a circular and upward movement.
Rinse with cold water and apply a moisturizer ( optional) 
Avoid coconut oil if you have very oily skin .
(Don’t use the pack if one is allergic to any of the ingredients above)
.
.
( music courtesy iTunes three ragas) .
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: “Glow baby glow” @prernastylefile
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“A quick face pack to brighten your skin “ ||
Ingredients ||
2 tbsps of yogurt (dahi)
2 soaked dates( khajur)
1/2 tsp orange peel powder ||
.
Take the yogurt first in a bowl , on the side grind the soaked dates make into a purée. ||
Mix the yogurt + dates purée + orange peel ||
Apply to your face ,neck and décolleté ||
Leave it for 15 mins , and then rinse it with cold water ||
Apply moisturizer or any oil of your choice ||
I have used Dinyar boxwalla moisturizer + few drop of face serum by @parogoodearth ||🌸 Benefits : The face pack helps brightens, reduce wrinkles, fine line , dark spots ,smoothens your skin and closes your pores ..☺️ This face pack you can store it in the fridge and use it for  the next 2 days , not more than that as the yogurt may go sour ||
Have a bright and beautiful day😊
(DM for any questions)
(Best way to make orange peel, dry some orange peels for 4-5 days , then grind them , and store them in a glass container)
